3 commission shall file with the department notice of and a copy of the federal application regarding any facility
4 subject to subsection (1). The state recommendation must be based on its study of the federal application and
5 other material gained through intervention in the federal proceeding.
6 (3) A person subject to the provisions of subsection (2) shall pay a fee to the department at the
7 time that an application is filed with the federal energy regulatory commission or nuclear regulatory commission.
8 The fee must be used by the department to carry out its responsibilities to develop a state recommendation and
9 participate as a party in any necessary federal proceeding to assert the state recommendation. The fee may not
10 exceed one-half the amount that could be assessed under 75-20-215. A fee prescribed by 75-20-215 may not
11 be assessed against a person paying a fee under this section.
12 (4) A person who fails to file a timely notice of and a copy of the federal application with the
13 department, preventing the department from timely compliance with this section and with the rules, statutes, or
14 procedures governing the proceedings before the federal energy regulatory commission or nuclear regulatory
15 commission, is subject to the provisions of 75-20-408."
